It's both. Have you tried using Enigmail or Mailvelope? Oh man. Enigmai=
l on=20
Windoze last time I checked couldn't handle passwords with non-ASCII ch=
ars (I=20
think this is *still true*). Mailvelope requires you to explicitly sele=
ct the=20
keys you want to encrypt your message with instead of at least pre-fill=
ing the=20
list with addressees of the e-mail.

The most usable PGP/GPG interface I've seen (and am still using, even t=
hough=20
there are other problems with the broader setup) is KMail+KGPG. And it =
could=20
*still* be much more convenient.

Simple thing that any such interface could do to make key=20
exchange/verification much easier and manageable to 90% of people is le=
tting=20
you use key fingerprints instead of e-mails in the To/CC fields:
http://rys.io/pl/122

